{"title":"Esker Lorax Ti is Reborn as Go-Everywhere Drop-Bar Mountain Bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/esker-lorax-ti-go-everywhere-drop-bar-mountain-bike/","date":1717083465000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike6-1536x864.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"864\" alt=\"Esker Lorax Ti bikepacking gravel adventure bike\" /></p>\n<p>First introduced back when Esker Cycles started as Advocate Cycles, the Lorax has gone through a bit of an evolution. Compared to the Esker Lorax Ti that was <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/esker-cycles-titanium-bikes-walden-ti-lorax-ti/\">reintroduced in 2022</a>, the third generation of the bike is the most capable yet. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike1.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike1-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Esker Lorax Ti bikepacking gravel adventure bike1\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike1-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike1.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Still constructed with a seamless, butted, and cold-shaped 3/2.5 titanium frame, the new Lorax Ti is shaped around geometry for a 120mm suspension fork or 495mm axle to crown. Coupled with massive tire clearance of 29 x 2.2 – 2.6″, this drop-bar mountain bike is ready to go everywhere you point it. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike3.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1536\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike3-1536x1536.jpg\" alt=\"Esker Lorax Ti bikepacking gravel adventure bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike3-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike3-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike3-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike3-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike3.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike4.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1536\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike4-1536x1536.jpg\" alt=\"Esker Lorax Ti bikepacking gravel adventure bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike4-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike4-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike4-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike4-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike4.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike5.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1536\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike5-1536x1536.jpg\" alt=\"Esker Lorax Ti bikepacking gravel adventure bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike5-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike5-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike5-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike5-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike5.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike13-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1536\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike13-1536x1536.jpg\" alt=\"Esker Lorax Ti bikepacking gravel adventure bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike13-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike13-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike13-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike13-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Esker-Lorax-Ti-bikepacking-gravel-adventure-bike13-2048x2048.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like other Esker bikes, the Lorax includes their Portage Dropout System which is also <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/esker-portage-dropouts-sram-udh-how-to-add-transmission-hayduke-or-japhy/\">now compatible with SRAM UDH</a>. Note that this frame utilized flat mount brakes. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame is also equipped with external cable routing, a threaded bottom bracket, 44mm head tube, and a whopping 22 attachment points for accessories, bags, fenders, etc. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Lorax-Geo-1-sheet-.1-e1717083068401.jpeg\"><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Lorax-Geo-1-sheet-.1.jpeg\" alt=\"Esker Lorax Ti bikepacking gravel adventure bike geometry\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Offered in four sizes, the frames offer internal dropper post routing, and have a claimed weight of 2,260g for a large with dropouts and necessary parts. Frame only pricing is set at $2,500, or you can add a Wolf Tooth Lithic Carbon fork for a total of $3,100. Complete builds start at $4,500 with many options. </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/esker-lorax-ti-go-everywhere-drop-bar-mountain-bike/\">Esker Lorax Ti is Reborn as Go-Everywhere Drop-Bar Mountain Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"18c8b423815f8548911a105bdd3c47dbc118b239ed4cb2b9f926cf696e37b96d","category":"Cycling"}